      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WATTS UP PARTYTIME (10) was far from disgraced when fifth behind superstar mare Keayang Zahara in the Group 1 Hammerhead Mile last start. Had won three of his other four starts this time in, two of them coming at this venue. Good enough to overcome a wide draw and win. GOTFEELINGSYOUKNOW (6) brings good form from Victoria where he added to a string of top-four finishes with a second at Melton last week. Placed the only time he raced here so could measure up along with KYVALLEY MAVEN (5) who also crosses the border with strong Melton form, finishing runner-up in his three starts since an easy win. CONSTANTINOPLE (11) is another that enjoys an easier assignment after tackling the Hammerhead Mile last start and his strike rate at this longer distance is encouraging. KRISTAL JOSSELYN (9) came from this barrier for second here last start, his best result in Australia so far. Could be ready to show his best now.",
